English Premier League giant, Manchester United, have contacted the agent of RB Leipzig defender, Ibrahima Konate. Konate is regarded as one of the brightest prospects in the German Bundesliga so far this season. According to the French newspaper, Le10Sport, the Red Devils have contacted Konate’s representative to clarify his situation at Leipzig and establish his desires ahead of a potential switch to Old Trafford. Konate’s current deal at Leipzig will expire in the summer of 2023. Leipzig is expected to demand a high fee for the 20-year-old centre-back.